  "body": "Hardhat v2.9.1 and v2.9.2, Node v16.14.2 on Windows Server 2019\r\n\r\nWhen I call `npx hardhat node` I see the `Started HTTP and WebSocket JSON-RPC server at http://127.0.0.1:8545/` message and after the account list nothing is displayed, no blocks are mined.\r\nI can't tell whether the node is actually running or still initializing, trying to fork the mainnet.\r\n\r\nAfter running the node I'm trying to connect to the node with Remix and I fails to connect with the following message:\r\n`Not possible to connect to the Web3 provider. Make sure the provider is running, a connection is open (via IPC or RPC) or that the provider plugin is properly configured.\r\n`\r\n\r\nI don't have that problem at another computer running Windows 10 with the same Hardhat and Node versions.\r\n\r\n\r\nConfig file:\r\n```\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  solidity: {\r\n    version: \"0.8.13\",\r\n    settings: {\r\n      optimizer: {\r\n        enabled: true,\r\n        runs: 200,\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n  networks: {\r\n    localhost: {\r\n      url: \"http://127.0.0.1:8545\"\r\n    },\r\n    hardhat: {\r\n      forking: {\r\n        url: eth_mainnet.url_alchemy,\r\n      },\r\n      mining: {\r\n        auto: false,\r\n        interval: 3000\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n```\r\n",
